Really nice cold noodles @potandnoodlesf which makes their chili oil in house. I didn’t know the difference until last year, well, at least, the difference in the US between cold noodles and dan Dan noodles is that the former uses a thinner noodle, and is in a spicy chili oil sauce with no meat; the latter is thicker noodles in a meat sauce with chili oil and also a key ingredient of a fermented type veggie commonly used in Sichuan, also, there’s usually roasted sesame sauce 芝麻酱 or peanut. When I was in China I was exposed to only one kind, which usually has no meat, chili oil, and sesame sauce so it’s like a marriage of the two 😁
.
. 📍: 650 Jackson St San Francisco
. 📷: @chinesefoodobsession .

Hong shao rou 红烧肉 is probably every Chinese kid’s favorite dish growing up, am I right? Each family has their own recipe for this braised pork belly dish, my family made theirs with bigger chunks of pork belly, lots of broth, not much sugar at all and sometimes added potatoes. Other recipes I’ve tried are sweeter, much more caramelized with little sauce. I think I may have found my favorite recipes 😋😋 instructions in IG stories and highlights 😋
.
📍: homemade
